@database BitmapClass
@index "Classes.guide/Main"

@Node Main "RxMUI - Bitmap Class"


Bitmap class    @{"Index" link "Classes.guide/Main"} @{"Super" link "AreaClass.guide/Main"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  The Bitmap class is used to display datatype picture files.

  Of course, you may give a Bitmap object a Frame, a Background
  and an Inputmode, to make it act like a button.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}File@{fg text}
  S I IND
  The name of a datatype picture file

  @{fg shine}Height@{fg text}
  N ISG
  The height of the image; let the class set it

  @{fg shine}Precision@{fg text}
  S ISG G2N
  One of:
     o Exact
     o Image
     o Icon
     o GUI

  @{fg shine}Transparent@{fg text}
  N ISG
  A color index

  @{fg shine}Width@{fg text}
  N ISG
  The width of the image; let the class set it

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  None defined

@EndNode
